ET.title: Sunoco LP Announces Sale Of West Texas Assets, Acquisition Of European Liquid Fuels Terminals, And Reaffirms 2024 Adjusted EBITDA Guidance Range
ET.text: Jan 11 (Reuters) - Sunoco Lp <SUN.N>::ANNOUNCES SALE OF WEST TEXAS ASSETS, ACQUISITION OF EUROPEAN LIQUID FUELS TERMINALS, AND REAFFIRMS 2024 ADJUSTED EBITDA GUIDANCE RANGE.ENTERED INTO A DEFINITIVE AGREEMENT FOR SALE OF 204 CONVENIENCE STORES TO 7-ELEVEN, INC..PROPOSED DEAL FOR APPROXIMATELY $1.0 BILLION.ENTERED INTO A DEFINITIVE AGREEMENT FOR SALE OF 204 CONVENIENCE STORES TO 7-ELEVEN, INC. ("7-ELEVEN") FOR APPROXIMATELY $1.0 BILLION.SUN WILL ALSO AMEND ITS EXISTING TAKE-OR-PAY FUEL SUPPLY AGREEMENT WITH 7-ELEVEN TO INCORPORATE ADDITIONAL FUEL GROSS PROFIT.ALSO ANNOUNCED ITS INTENTION TO ACQUIRE ONE HUNDRED PERCENT OF EQUITY INTEREST IN ZENITH ENERGY NETHERLANDS AMSTERDAM B.V..PREVIOUSLY ANNOUNCED 2024 EBITDA GUIDANCE RANGE OF $975 MILLION TO $1 BILLION REMAINS UNCHANGED.EXPECTS EUROPEAN TERMINALS ACQUISITION TO BE ACCRETIVE TO UNITHOLDERS IN FIRST YEAR OF OWNERSHIP.EUROPEAN TERMINALS ACQUISITION  WILL BE FUNDED USING AMOUNTS AVAILABLE UNDER SUN'S REVOLVING CREDIT FACILITY.
